  <h3>Next 2 Weeks</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>For any stranded model (no replacement identified): start benchmarking candidates. Budget $1K–$2K for testing.</li>
    <li>For Assistants API users: read the <a href="https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/assistants-migration">Responses API migration guide</a>. Estimate integration cost.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="guide-section">
  <h3>Next 30 Days</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Finalize replacement model choice. Lock cost forecast.</li>
    <li>Start dual-running if possible (A/B test on production traffic).</li>
    <li>Assign migration owner and commit to completion date.</li>
    <li>Update your annual FinOps budget: add $4K–$12K per model migration + $200–$500/month ongoing monitoring.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="guide-section">
  <h3>Before EOL Date</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Complete regression testing. Go live on replacement.</li>
    <li>Set up post-migration monitoring. Watch for quality drift, cost anomalies.</li>
    <li>Document the migration: what broke, what cost more than expected, lessons for next time.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

